This paper discusses the training and classification of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the geometry of decision regions and the role of weight and bias terms in the formation of gradients. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also touches on regularization and subsampling, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
